headline: How the Story for GE Is Changing as Analysts Boost Their Outlook and Reassess Risks
summary: General Electric stock has recently seen its consensus analyst price target rise from $327.29 to $343.57, as market expectations for the company’s performance improve. This higher valuation follows analysts’ increasing optimism about GE’s commercial engine division and the broader aerospace industry outlook. However, some remain cautious amidst ongoing supply chain and production risks. Stay tuned to learn how investors can monitor shifts in GE’s evolving narrative and stay ahead of future...
